Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.88,0:00:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.97,0:00:15.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.39,0:00:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think the Inubushi household is around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.35,0:00:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.73,0:00:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inubushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.73,0:00:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What business do you have with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.27,0:00:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're just thinking about solving a\Nlittle issue/involving a puppy's curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.99,0:00:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be frank with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.32,0:00:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had better give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.36,0:00:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you stick your neck into that business\Nfor no good reason, you'll get badly burnt.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.08,0:00:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, where's the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.12,0:00:52.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see a roof that looks like a\Ncastle half way up that mountain, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the Inubushi home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.97,0:01:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A manor put under a curse by a dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.16,0:01:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Causing your eyelids to swell and permeating your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.22,0:01:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tear drops serve as a prelude to a wealth of drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.75,0:01:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the mystery behind the blazing dog that has pounced on the accursed Inubushi home?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.27,0:01:11.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.98,0:01:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.86,0:01:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.07,0:01:24.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sky I saw back then gave me a flashback For an instant, I felt you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.08,0:01:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite my heart nearly being shuttered, your face kept popping up in the sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.88,0:01:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why why why Though I already knew I couldn't say it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.93,0:01:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lie lie I want you to stay with me I want your love
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.52,0:01:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? You noticed it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.61,0:01:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops isn't that right? l'm crying, am I not?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:02:01.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? I can never forget our love
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.37,0:02:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops tear drops Solve this mystery tear drops
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.25,0:02:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Overflowing with tears I think I've become a little more honest with myself
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.38,0:02:20.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the starry night, I say: "I believe, forever my dream"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.64,0:02:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quietly my tear drops
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.89,0:02:28.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? You noticed it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.73,0:02:32.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? I'm crying, am I not?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.06,0:02:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? This is my last love
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.94,0:02:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops tear drops It's only for you that my tear drops
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.45,0:02:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Conan is brought to you by these sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.55,0:03:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori Heiji brought in a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.88,0:03:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The adopted children of Inubushi Tsunechika, the\NInubushi Group president who died five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.31,0:03:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One by one departed this world in bizarre ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.10,0:03:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, they claimed it's the deed of\Nan aflamed apparition that resembled a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.23,0:03:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because one of the adopted children was\Nacquaintances with Kazuha's mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.65,0:03:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went with Hattori to hear his story out, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To my surprise, his name was "Kudou Shinichi".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.74,0:03:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the kanji was different, it sounded just like my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.70,0:03:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, before we got to ask him about the story...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.91,0:03:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone murdered Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and\Ndisguised it as a charcoal-burning suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.21,0:03:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on earth is the identity of the culprit\Nwho called themselves "a vengeful spirit"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.26,0:03:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's the meaning behind the pearl that\Nwas held in the mouth of Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s corpse?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.14,0:03:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What can it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.35,0:03:53.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,INUBUSHI CASTLE\NTHE ABLAZED DEMON DOG
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.33,0:03:53.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,(WILL-0'-THE-WISP CHAPTER)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.02,0:03:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well Heiji, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.69,0:04:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you said about that Shinichi guy who was\Nthe adopted son of the Inubushi family..
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.03,0:04:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a pearl that fell out of his corpse's mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.45,0:04:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.24,0:04:11.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He likely bit the pearl off of his necktie's pin in his final moments...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.29,0:04:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking that he'd leave a clue about the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.75,0:04:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.37,0:04:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.25,0:04:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since that man's saliva was on the necktie\Npın as well, it could be a dying message!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:23.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It could be"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.55,0:04:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not a sure thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.24,0:04:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.43,0:04:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His saliva was on it, but there was no trace of it having been bitten.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.35,0:04:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the pearl may have been loosely attached\Nın such a way that it was easy to remove...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.21,0:04:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.23,0:04:38.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be that the culprit wanted to deliver a message...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.82,0:04:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And forced the victim to hold the pearl in his mouth on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.19,0:04:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Heiji-niichan?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.95,0:04:48.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two are getting along well as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.62,0:04:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True, it's like he's Heiji's assistant!'
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.12,0:04:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enough with the "assistant"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.00,0:04:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well either way, it's the work of someone with\Nquite a grudge against the Inubushi family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.46,0:05:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since despite Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} having already given up his portion\Nof the Inubushi inheritance and returning to Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.09,0:05:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He still was murdered by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.47,0:05:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.55,0:05:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wealthy old Inubushi Tsunechika passed his\Ninheritance to his wife Satomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who has fallen ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.69,0:05:21.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit's intention was to increase their own share of the\Nınheritance by decreasing the number of adopted children...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.36,0:05:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It should have nothing to do with Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:27.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, there were eight adopted children, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.36,0:05:28.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.41,0:05:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although they are all from different mothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.53,0:05:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I think, perhaps one of the eight children may really be a fake...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.91,0:05:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who only wants to satisfy some sort of grudge?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.71,0:05:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.83,0:05:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the real children could also hold a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.34,0:05:43.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Given they were neglected for so many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.21,0:05:45.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.42,0:05:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of those eight people, which ones are dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.09,0:05:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.89,0:05:53.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who was murdered in a way to look like\Na charcoal-burning suicide was Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.35,0:05:57.81,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Miwako\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.39,0:05:57.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And before that, a lady by the name of\NMiwako was found dead near a marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.69,0:06:02.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Despite having no apparent heat source,\Nthe grass around the marsh was burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:06.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And the first victim was a man by the name\Nof Keiji who fell off a cliff to his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.65,0:06:07.74,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Keiji\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.74,0:06:09.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He said he was chased by a dog on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.12,0:06:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're scared, you could have stayed home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.29,0:06:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:20.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After hearing a scary story, you naturally\Nwant to find out what's behind it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.79,0:06:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I think as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.34,0:06:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it is still scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.09,0:06:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.30,0:06:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you want me to go back, it's too late to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.26,0:06:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop, go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.97,0:06:30.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a cliff up ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.05,0:06:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So close...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.11,0:06:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.11,0:06:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you see the sign posted a while back?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.86,0:06:50.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.45,0:06:52.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone also fell and died not long ago, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.45,0:06:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're actually on our way to the Inubushi\Nhome in order to investigate that accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.20,0:07:03.63,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Miyuki (28)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.62,0:07:02.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm actually a member of that Inubushi family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.92,0:07:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really does look like a Japanese castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.80,0:07:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hear that people in this area even call it "Inubushi Castle".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.72,0:07:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like a manor that's been\Ncursed by a demon dog at all, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.72,0:07:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.98,0:07:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.61,0:07:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.86,0:07:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An Akita Inu!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.19,0:07:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop it Hachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.86,0:07:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These people are a police officer and his companions\Nwho have come to investigate Keiji-niisan's accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.37,0:07:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, l'm not a police officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.33,0:07:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who should stop, Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.63,0:07:49.59,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Takako (47)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.38,0:07:48.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,When a dog barks for no reason, and you call its name or pat it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.71,0:07:51.34,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The dog will mistakenly think it's being praised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.34,0:07:53.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to say this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.76,0:07:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Takako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.18,0:08:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what business do you have with us, Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.14,0:08:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A few days ago another officer came and\Nsaid "That was definitely an accident!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.19,0:08:05.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he simply left, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.73,0:08:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, l'm not a polic—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.65,0:08:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, something happened that made us\Nthink it may not have been an accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.03,0:08:14.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we came all the way here to get the whole story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.61,0:08:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.57,0:08:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.20,0:08:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that they're talking about\NShinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who died in Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.83,0:08:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's what Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said before leaving this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.25,0:08:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That nonsensical story about someone using a cursed dog\Nengulfed in flames to root out all those with Inubushi blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.30,0:08:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there is no curse, so don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.97,0:08:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, if our mother hears a story like that, she will be sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.27,0:08:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is Satomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.69,0:08:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought she had been hospitalized...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.06,0:08:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:52.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she's bedridden and can barely speak at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.03,0:08:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She suffered a stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.53,0:09:00.33,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Satomi (74)\NHead of the Inubushi Family
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.07,0:09:00.33,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,She's been like this ever since she collapsed a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.20,0:09:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been better for her to have been hospitalized...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.12,0:09:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since she's getting on in years, we decided to care for her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:11.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My name is Inubushi Tomoaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:14.09,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Tomoaki (42)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:14.09,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A general practitioner at the nearby Inubushi Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be that you're also one of the eight adopted children?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.30,0:09:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.30,0:09:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the hospital I was employed at\Nshut down, I was left out in the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.52,0:09:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when Mother Satomi rescued me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.81,0:09:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.81,0:09:29.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Satomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.81,0:09:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About who reeks of being an impostor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.07,0:09:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, not in particular...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:39.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't that Shinichi guy have been an impostor himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:46.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Yoshiya (34)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.37,0:09:43.16,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He was so scared of rumors about that imaginary demon dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.16,0:09:46.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And left this Inubushi household — a traitor, that's why!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.79,0:09:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with you, Yoshiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.75,0:09:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't use such uncouth words in Mother's presence!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.46,0:09:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She couldn't have heard me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.38,0:09:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's sleeping anyway, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.42,0:09:56.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one person left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.13,0:09:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The eight adopted children!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.84,0:10:01.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were three who died, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:05.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there should be five remaining, but we only have...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.10,0:10:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Takako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.02,0:10:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomoaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and the guy outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.77,0:10:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, these four people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.86,0:10:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.94,0:10:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be one more person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.19,0:10:19.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that they sustained injuries to their\Nface and are wearing some sort of weird mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.16,0:10:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is not The Inugami Clan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.74,0:10:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That other person is Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:29.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went to the cleaners a Iittle way from here\Nto pick up some clothes we had sent out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.17,0:10:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about some tea while we wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.59,0:10:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it'd be hard to hear the whole story without everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.80,0:10:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, why not tell them the demon dog's myth\Nthat's been passed down through the Inubushi family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.47,0:10:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Myth?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.06,0:10:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They burned it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.31,0:10:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the ancestors of this family burned a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.35,0:10:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.48,0:10:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was originated in the Meiji era.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.19,0:11:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the only daughter of the Inubushi family suddenly\Nwent missing, they had everyone in the village search for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.20,0:11:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the Inubushi family dog showed up unexpectedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.57,0:11:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was grasping the daughter in its\Njaws, gravely injured and near death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.37,0:11:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The enraged master whipped the dog endlessly...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.37,0:11:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And on top of all that, set its body on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.29,0:11:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But later, the daughter regained consciousness...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.84,0:11:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told her father that the dog had come to her rescue\Nwhen she had gotten lost and collapsed in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.05,0:11:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He regretted his actions, and erected a proper grave for the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.02,0:11:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.27,0:11:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fire broke out a few days later and the only one\Nto not make it out in time and die was the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.98,0:11:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since then, it's been said that the Inubushi\Nfamily has been cursed by a fiery demon dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.24,0:11:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounds just like a fairy tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.15,0:11:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, does that grave really exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.99,0:11:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's below the cliff that your car\Nalmost fell from this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.87,0:11:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want, shall we go see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.17,0:11:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.67,0:12:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says it's Fusatarou's grave, the heroic\Nand beloved dog of the Inubushi family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.17,0:12:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This being the case, whenever a fiery dog appears...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.26,0:12:07.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People probably think it's this Fusatarou's curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm paying my proper respects so I don't get cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.60,0:12:12.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.89,0:12:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing as curses, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.27,0:12:19.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, about the cliff Keiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fell off from, could this be the one?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.40,0:12:20.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was right above this grave...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.04,0:12:39.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hang in there, Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.09,0:12:41.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.09,0:12:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is she the remaining adopted child!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.67,0:12:46.22,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Saki (35)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.28,0:12:45.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.30,0:12:46.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,On fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.45,0:12:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dog on fire!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.60,0:12:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, call the police and an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.43,0:12:53.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll go with Uncle Kogorou in the car to the top of the cliff!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.98,0:12:57.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't leave us girls waiting here alone in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.98,0:13:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to go to the top of the cliff, it'd be\Nfaster than by car if you used the animal trail!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.19,0:13:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the casef lead the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.07,0:13:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, you two wait here with Uncle Kogorou!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, the top of the cliff!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.63,0:13:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.96,0:13:25.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no smell of oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.68,0:13:31.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost as if a fiery dog just passed through.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.43,0:13:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.94,0:13:43.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Flaming footprints, you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.19,0:13:45.82,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You're saying that kind of weird thing was atop the cliff?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.57,0:13:48.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.28,0:13:52.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There were sets of scattered flames starting about\Ntwenty meters back from the edge of the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.87,0:13:56.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It looked as if a fiery demon dog had run through.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.00,0:14:01.38,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But you didn't see an actual demon dog, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.38,0:14:06.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I say someone must've scattered oil and set it aflame\Nto make it look like there really was a demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.49,0:14:07.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.47,0:14:09.68,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any scent of oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.68,0:14:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the space between each fire got wider\Nas it got closer to the edge of the cliff...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.47,0:14:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flames became larger as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.35,0:14:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as if whatever the burning object was\Ngrew bigger as it passed through.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.60,0:14:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.61,0:14:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.69,0:14:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.86,0:14:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cursed demon dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.57,0:14:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really exists, right!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.65,0:14:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who fell from the cliff was saying "a dog's on fire"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.45,0:14:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.83,0:14:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way something like a demon dog exists in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.75,0:14:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.21,0:14:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit just did something clever to make\Nit seem as if there were a demon dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.42,0:14:45.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, they could put the blame on the demon dog for their crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.67,0:14:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.51,0:14:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're in an era where TV broadcasting goes digital, yet\Nyou're still worked up over something like a demon dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.47,0:14:55.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you totally fall off the wagon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.93,0:14:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.52,0:15:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that was a pun with digital and\Ndid you totally that I just thought up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.11,0:15:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.69,0:15:07.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's with the Gunma prefectural police...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.69,0:15:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're in Gunma after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.49,0:15:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.24,0:15:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who just fell from the cliff?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.66,0:15:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I only heard she was being\Ntransported to a hospital by ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.21,0:15:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was my hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.29,0:15:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they just contacted me on my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.29,0:15:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She passed away in the ambulance...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.55,0:15:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.26,0:15:33.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know who's pulling the strings behind that demon dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.76,0:15:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But sure looks like someone's trying\Nto mess with our Inubushi family.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.39,0:15:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.72,0:15:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Given that out of the eight adopted children...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.68,0:15:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Half, or rather four of us are no longer here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.56,0:15:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sof for the time being...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.06,0:15:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of the four of you remaining, can I hear the alibis of you three?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.65,0:15:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fell from that cliff around 7 PM,\Nwhat were you doing and your whereabouts?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.70,0:16:00.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was with us at the bottom\Nof the cliff to see that dog's grave...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.37,0:16:02.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So her alibi is solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.00,0:16:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,7:00 is around when I was taking a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.75,0:16:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went out for a bit to check on Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nbecause she shouldn't have been that late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.42,0:16:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even now, she still got lost quite often.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.76,0:16:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at Mother's side, taking her temperature and\Nblood pressure and giving her a liquid diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.81,0:16:27.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although, I don't think she'll be able to\Nverify that given that she's bedridden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.23,0:16:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two also don't seem to have anyone who can verify your alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.61,0:16:39.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We usually have three caretakers around,\Nbut they've all gone home for a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.83,0:16:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.95,0:16:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asking this is my duty as a police officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't take my job from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.54,0:16:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.33,0:16:47.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This gentleman...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.67,0:16:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not with the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.42,0:16:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I completely forgot to mention...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This gentleman here is Mouri Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.01,0:16:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mo...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.55,0:16:57.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.93,0:16:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kogorou?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.18,0:17:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're the great detective Mouri Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.85,0:17:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.60,0:17:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.69,0:17:06.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The atmosphere sure has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.86,0:17:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were just a bit surprised is all...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.52,0:17:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before the late Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left this household, he told us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.45,0:17:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he already asked an acquaintance\Nthat was affiliated with the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To resolve the mysterious events unfolding in the Inubushi home...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.87,0:17:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to brace ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.45,0:17:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to think he was referring to the famous Sleeping Kogorou!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.96,0:17:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I was actually the one he asked for, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.30,0:17:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, on the day Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was\Nmurdered in his home in Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.88,0:17:39.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had, any of you happened to have gone to Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.68,0:17:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All four of us did go to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.56,0:17:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We all went to persuade him to return to the Inubushi home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.19,0:17:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he seemed to be suspecting one of us, we\Nalso wanted to ask him what his reason was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.78,0:17:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he looked so scared and didn't tell us anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.53,0:18:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if he stayed quiet precisely because one of us was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.08,0:18:08.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard about Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death once we returned here\Nfrom Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had been watching the house for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.50,0:18:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the four of you were together the entire time in Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.17,0:18:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.25,0:18:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went together, but came back separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.97,0:18:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway will you let us know already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.09,0:18:23.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About what, you learned from Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.35,0:18:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you said there was something related to Keiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who had passed away earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.94,0:18:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't know whether it's related or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.65,0:18:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the murdered Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had it in his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.69,0:18:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pearl that had been attached to his necktie pin!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.45,0:18:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.87,0:18:44.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.08,0:18:48.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was also something lying next to Keiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwho had fallen from the cliff like Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pachinko bali!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.08,0:18:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pachinko ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.58,0:18:55.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that old guy loved pachinko...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.50,0:18:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought it had simply fallen out of his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.42,0:18:59.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.30,0:19:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, on the ground near the marsh where Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.51,0:19:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a ping pong ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.39,0:19:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sphere, sphere, sphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:12.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the pearl wasn't a dying message...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.73,0:19:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But rather, a message deliberately left by the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.73,0:19:19.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.07,0:19:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was also the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.82,0:19:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found it after Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been taken away in the ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.58,0:19:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing that had rolled next to the dog's grave — a marble!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.16,0:19:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A marble?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.58,0:19:31.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have it with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.21,0:19:35.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought it was someone's offering,\Nso we put it on the grave and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.13,0:19:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.88,0:19:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going to go take a look at that marble.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to come with us, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.05,0:19:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also have something l'd like to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.34,0:19:46.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, wait here quietly and be good!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.76,0:19:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.27,0:19:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we want to go too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.48,0:19:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're the ones who found it, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.48,0:19:53.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you can tag along...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.06,0:19:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to go meet the demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.73,0:19:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.28,0:19:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Barging in on all of you like this, and\Neven having you treat us to dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.37,0:20:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.54,0:20:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Heiji and the others will be back before dawn...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.94,0:20:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.38,0:20:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, it'II be tough from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.30,0:20:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meal preparation and cleaning was mostly done by Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.05,0:20:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did all those...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.18,0:20:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there anything we can do to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.31,0:20:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, can I have you guys feed Hachi?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.35,0:20:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.98,0:20:41.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked Takako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others, but they refused to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.57,0:20:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.95,0:20:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Takako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} seems like she's used to dealing with dogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.37,0:20:53.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard thatTakako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} raised dogs before\Nshe came here, so she's familiar with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.46,0:20:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it seems she's been busy making\Ncalls regarding funeral arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.46,0:21:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomoaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was bitten by a dog a\Nlong time ago, and is aversive to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he'd always tremble in fear, Hachi would bark at him a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.05,0:21:08.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is allergic to dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.35,0:21:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said if a dog's near him, he can't\Nstop sneezing or having a runny nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.06,0:21:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it was always Takako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\NSaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, or myself who fed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.15,0:21:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But can you guys do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.23,0:21:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the doghouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.32,0:21:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a little far...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.41,0:21:27.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Far?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.61,0:21:29.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean it's outside the house...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.62,0:21:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.91,0:21:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's at the edge of the yard, but it's surrounded by a fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.12,0:21:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even a demon dog couldn't get in!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.71,0:21:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.80,0:21:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite a large yard, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.97,0:21:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that the doghouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.27,0:21:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.14,0:21:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hachi's there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.81,0:22:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hachi, we've brought your dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.03,0:22:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't leave anything behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.03,0:22:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.41,0:22:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only the demon dog were like this too...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.66,0:22:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.09,0:22:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.42,0:22:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something light up over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.58,0:23:02.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I recall is that blue moonlight
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.04,0:23:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your retreating figure waved to me, as the light of the moon took you away that day
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.59,0:23:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From my heart, from my heart, I want to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.47,0:23:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I love you, I love you - a feeling that cannot be reached
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.19,0:23:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were it a dream, were it a dream, I could have met with you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.86,0:23:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although my wishes cannot come true
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.49,0:23:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mischievous magic on the moonlit night - you're imprisoned in the shade of the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.83,0:23:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the new moon obscured by darkness, your figure escapes my sight
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.64,0:23:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you're so close
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.00,0:24:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Conan was brought to you by these sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.22,0:24:19.50,Signs,,0,0,0,,Onion
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.80,0:24:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
